Cape Town - "WTF is Stage 6?" This was the common reaction shared by many South Africans on Monday evening when Eskom implemented Stage 6 load shedding for the first time. The extensive power cuts came after Eskom started the day with Stage 2 load shedding, before moving to Stage 4 at around 10am, and ending with the announcement that Stage 6 would kick in at 6pm. "We regret and sincerely apologise that stage 4 loadshedding will move to Stage 6 loadshedding as from 18:00 today, as a result of a shortage of capacity. This follows a technical problem at Medupi Power Station impacting additional generation supply. The heavy rains has caused coal handling and operational problems at several power stations," Eskom said. "Stage 6 requires 6000MW to be rotationally loadshed." Many South Africans took to social media in disbelief that Stage 6 had been implemented, as well as sharing their confusion as many of their apps and only had information on load shedding stages 1-4. In typical fashion, South Africans dealt with their frustrations the only way they knew how - humour:     What in the fresh Hell is #Stage6 Loadshedding? pic.twitter.com/bHwYd1QiwZ     Wtf is stage 6 load shedding ğŸ˜­     WTF even is load shedding stage 6???Iâ€™m expecting a boss fight at stage 10.     Stage 6 load shedding is when they come into your house and blow out the candles     this group of white girls in front of me are talking about how load shedding isn't even that bad because "regardless of stage 4 or 6 we don't even feel it by us, there's really no difference" and walahi I'm about to rol ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚     Johannesburg views before and after Eskom implements Stage 6 load shedding ğŸ˜…. pic.twitter.com/MfaKaLnHTC     Stage 6 is a reminder that load shedding has more stages than your relationship.     All the babies born during stage 6 load shedding are gonna grow in to Bane.     stage 6 load shedding is when eskom sends people to your home to physically pull out the plugs     Can someone p